  "prompt": "How can an international student become a teacher in Scotland?",
  "response": "To become a teacher in Scotland as an international student, you'll need to follow these steps:\n\n1. Qualifications\n- Have a bachelor's degree\n- Complete a recognized teaching qualification (PGDE/PGCE)\n- Have your international qualifications assessed by the General Teaching Council for Scotland (GTCS)\n\n2. Language Requirements\n- Demonstrate English language proficiency (IELTS or equivalent)\n- Typically need an overall IELTS score of 7.0 with at least 6.5 in each component\n\n3. Visa Requirements\n- Obtain a Tier 2 (General) Work Visa or Student Visa\n- Secure a job offer from a Scottish school or complete a teaching course in Scotland\n\n4. Teaching Qualification Options\n- One-year Postgraduate Diploma in Education (PGDE) at a Scottish university\n- Complete a teaching course accredited by GTCS\n\n5. Registration\n- Register with the General Teaching Council for Scotland\n- Undergo a PVG (Protection of Vulnerable Groups) scheme check\n\n6. Additional Steps\n- Provide proof of identity and qualifications\n- Pay registration fees\n- Meet professional standards set by GTCS\n\nRecommended universities offering teaching qualifications include University of Edinburgh, University of Glasgow, and University of Aberdeen.",
